Transaction Review — Spec V2
Location: leedavis-irl/monarch-slack-integration (standalone repo, runs independently of Iji)
Slack identity: Posts as Iji (same bot token), but is a discrete background process — not conversational
Status: Shipped, running in production. This spec documents current behavior and defines V2 improvements.

What It Does (Current / V1)
The Transaction Review process surfaces uncategorized Monarch Money transactions to the household for collaborative review — all without anyone needing to open the Monarch app.
Weekly batch flow:

Cron job fires every Sunday at 6 PM
Fetches all transactions from Monarch with needsReview = true
Posts each transaction one at a time to the designated Slack channel
Household adults select a category from a dropdown; Monarch is updated and the transaction marked as reviewed

Adult Pay Backs flow:
When "Adult Pay Backs" is selected as a category, Iji follows up asking which household member is claiming the transaction. Ownership is tracked locally in data/state.json (Monarch has no owner field). A weekly balance summary shows who owes what net across all tracked paybacks.
Data store: Local data/state.json on EC2 — tracks posted transaction IDs (to prevent duplicates) and payback ownership records.
Auth: Monarch uses a reverse-engineered GraphQL API with session-based auth + TOTP MFA. Session token is cached; re-auth happens automatically on 401.

Known Gaps & V2 Requirements
1. Health Monitor (required)
The process currently runs silently — there is no alerting if it fails, falls behind, or loses its Monarch session. Add the following:
Startup check: On each cron invocation, verify the Monarch session is valid before doing any work. If invalid, attempt re-auth (including TOTP generation). If re-auth fails, send a Signal message to Lee: "Transaction Review: Monarch authentication failed. Manual re-auth required." Do not proceed with the batch.
Post-run summary to Lee: After each weekly run, send Lee a brief Signal DM summarizing: transactions posted, any errors encountered, session status. Format: "Transaction Review complete: 14 transactions posted, 0 errors. Next run: Sunday."
Stale detection: If no transactions have been posted in 14 days (two missed Sundays), send Lee a Signal alert. This catches silent cron failures, not just auth errors.
Signal, not Slack: Health alerts go to Lee via Signal, not to the household Slack channel. Household channel is for financial content only.
2. State File Resilience (required)
The current data/state.json is a single file on EC2 with no backup. If the instance is rebuilt or the file is lost, the bot will re-post all historical transactions.
V2 requirement: On startup, if state.json is missing or corrupted, log a warning and start fresh — do not crash. Add a simple backup: copy state.json to state.json.bak before each write.
3. Rename & Reframe (documentation only)
The repo is named monarch-slack-integration — functional but opaque. Internal documentation and any future references should use the name Transaction Review. No code changes required.
4. Frequency Option (backlog)
Currently hardcoded to weekly Sunday runs. Future consideration: make the schedule configurable via env var, or add a manual trigger Iji can invoke. Not required for V2.

